results.occurrenceRemarks: Brian Patrick found and collected this female at this site on Birdlings Flat this morning. I photographed it when he released it later in the day. Brian mentioned that this is the latest in the season he's ever found an adult Canterbury boulder copper. Note the ant in the last photo. It grabbed onto one of the antennae but was shaken loose by the butterfly. (I've added it as a separate observation).
